# Enterprise ERP System - Implementation Walkthrough

## Executive Summary

Successfully transformed the college management system into a **production-grade Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) system** following 2025 SaaS standards.

**Key Achievements:**
- ✅ **19 normalized database tables** with RBAC infrastructure
- ✅ **5-tier role hierarchy** (Super Admin → Employee) with 19 granular permissions
- ✅ **Complete attendance workflow** with admin locking mechanism
- ✅ **Comprehensive audit logging** tracking all critical actions
- ✅ **14+ admin APIs** for full system control
- ✅ **Enterprise-grade authentication** with permission enforcement

---

## Database Architecture

### Schema Overview

Created`[schema_erp_v3.sql](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20new%20updae%202.0/ldm_test/dist/php_backend/sql/schema_erp_v3.sql)` with **19 tables**:

#### Core Authentication & RBAC
| Table | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `users` | Enhanced user accounts with suspension tracking |
| `roles` | 5 system roles with priority hierarchy |
| `user_roles` | Multi-role assignment per user |
| `permissions` | 19 granular resource-action permissions |
| `role_permissions` | RBAC mapping |

#### Academic Entities
| Table | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `students` | Student profiles linked to users |
| `teachers` | Teacher profiles with employee codes |
| `employees` | Non-teaching staff |
| `classes` | Academic year/semester/section |
| `subjects` | Course catalog |
| `class_subjects` | Teacher-subject-class assignments |

#### Attendance Management
| Table | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `attendance` | Student attendance with **locking mechanism** |

#### Audit & Compliance
| Table | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `audit_logs` | Complete trail of admin actions with JSON old/new values |

#### Existing Enhanced Tables
| Table | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `notices`, `notifications`, `contact_messages`, `website_content`, `gallery`, `marquee` | Enhanced from v2 schema |

### RBAC Verification

```sql
-- Role hierarchy confirmed:
super_admin:  19 permissions (Full access)
admin:        19 permissions (Full administrative access)
teacher:       5 permissions (attendance + classes)
student:       2 permissions (read-only)
employee:      1 permission  (notices read)
```

**Permission Distribution:**

**Super Admin & Admin:**
- `users.*` (create, read, update, delete, suspend, reset_password)
- `attendance.*` (create, read, update, delete, lock, override)
- `notices.*`, `classes.manage`, `reports.generate`, `audit_logs.read`

**Teacher:**
- `attendance.create`, `attendance.read`, `attendance.update`
- `notices.read`, `classes.manage`

**Student:**
- `attendance.read`, `notices.read`

**Employee:**
- `notices.read`

