## API Endpoints

### Admin APIs - User Management

#### [POST /api/admin/users/create.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20new%20updae%202.0/ldm_test/dist/php_backend/api/admin/users/create.php)

**Create user accounts with role-specific data**

**Request Body:**
```json
{
  "username": "john_doe",
  "email": "john@college.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123",
  "full_name": "John Doe",
  "phone_number": "9876543210",
  "role": "teacher",
  "employee_code": "TCH001",
  "department": "Pharmacy",
  "designation": "Assistant Professor"
}
```

**Features:**
- Automatic bcrypt password hashing
- Role-specific table creation (students/teachers/employees)
- Transaction safety
- Duplicate email/username detection
- Audit logging

#### [POST /api/admin/users/suspend.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20new%20updae%202.0/ldm_test/dist/php_backend/api/admin/users/suspend.php)

**Suspend/unsuspend user accounts**

**Request Body:**
```json
{
  "user_id": 5,
  "action": "suspend",
  "reason": "Disciplinary action - pending investigation"
}
```

**Features:**
- Cannot suspend own account
- Tracks suspended_by admin
- Suspension reason logging
- Audit trail with before/after states

#### [POST /api/admin/users/reset_password.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20new%20updae%202.0/ldm_test/dist/php_backend/api/admin/users/reset_password.php)

**Force password reset for any user**

**Request Body:**
```json
{
  "user_id": 5,
  "new_password": "NewPassword456"
}
```

**Features:**
- Admin can reset any user password
- Automatic bcrypt hashing
- Audit logging (without password in logs)

---

### Admin APIs - Attendance Management

#### [POST /api/admin/attendance/lock.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20new%20updae%202.0/ldm_test/dist/php_backend/api/admin/attendance/lock.php)

**Lock/unlock attendance records**

**Request Body:**
```json
{
  "attendance_ids": [1, 2, 3, 4, 5],
  "action": "lock"
}
```

**Features:**
- Bulk lock/unlock operation
- Once locked, teachers **cannot edit**
- Only admins can unlock
- Detailed audit logging per record

#### [POST /api/admin/attendance/override.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20new%20updae%202.0/ldm_test/dist/php_backend/api/admin/attendance/override.php)

**Override attendance records (even locked ones)**

**Request Body:**
```json
{
  "attendance_id": 1,
  "new_status": "present",
  "remarks": "Admin correction - student was present"
}
```

**Features:**
- Admin can edit **even locked** attendance
- Valid statuses: `present`, `absent`, `late`, `excused`
- Audit logging with old → new status
- Student/subject/date context in audit

---

### Teacher APIs

#### [POST /api/teacher/attendance/mark.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20new%20updae%202.0/ldm_test/dist/php_backend/api/teacher/attendance/mark.php)

**Mark student attendance**

**Request Body:**
```json
{
  "class_id": 1,
  "subject_id": 3,
  "attendance_date": "2026-01-29",
  "attendance_records": [
    {"student_id": 1, "status": "present"},
    {"student_id": 2, "status": "absent", "remarks": "Sick leave"},
    {"student_id": 3, "status": "late"}
  ]
}
```

**Features:**
- Verifies teacher is assigned to class-subject
- Cannot edit locked attendance (skips)
- Updates existing or creates new records
- Upsert pattern for flexibility

---

### Student APIs

#### [GET /api/student/attendance/view.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20new%20updae%202.0/ldm_test/dist/php_backend/api/student/attendance/view.php)

**View own attendance records (read-only)**

**Query Parameters:**
- `subject_id` (optional): Filter by subject
- `start_date` (optional): From date
- `end_date` (optional): To date

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "student_id": "STU2026001",
    "records": [...],
    "statistics": {
      "total": 45,
      "present": 40,
      "absent": 5,
      "percentage": 88.89
    }
  }
}
```

---

### Audit Logging

#### [GET /api/admin/audit/logs.php](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20new%20updae%202.0/ldm_test/dist/php_backend/api/admin/audit/logs.php)

**View system audit trail**

**Query Parameters:**
- `user_id`: Filter by admin user
- `action`: Filter by action type
- `resource_type`: Filter by resource (users, attendance, etc.)
- `start_date`, `end_date`: Date range
- `limit`, `offset`: Pagination

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "logs": [
      {
        "id": 1,
        "username": "admin",
        "full_name": "System Administrator",
        "action": "override_attendance",
        "resource_type": "attendance",
        "resource_id": 5,
        "description": "Admin overrode attendance for John Doe (STU001) - Pharmacology on 2026-01-29: absent → present",
        "old_value": {"status": "absent"},
        "new_value": {"status": "present"},
        "ip_address": "192.168.1.100",
        "created_at": "2026-01-29 14:30:00"
      }
    ],
    "pagination": {
      "total": 150,
      "limit": 50,
      "offset": 0,
      "has_more": true
    }
  }
}
```

