## Attendance Workflow

### Workflow Diagram

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Teacher Marks Attendance] --> B{Is Locked?}
    B -->|No| C[Save/Update Attendance]
    B -->|Yes| D[Skip - Cannot Edit]
    C --> E[Admin Reviews Attendance]
    E --> F{Needs Changes?}
    F -->|Yes| G[Admin Override]
    F -->|No| H[Admin Locks Record]
    G --> H
    H --> I[Student Views Read-Only]
    I --> J{Teacher Tries Edit?}
    J -->|Yes| K[Blocked - Locked by Admin]
    J -->|No| L[No Action Needed]
```

### Key Rules

1. **Teacher can mark**: Only for assigned class-subject combinations
2. **Teacher CANNOT edit**: Locked attendance records
3. **Admin can override**: Any attendance, even if locked
4. **Admin can lock/unlock**: Bulk or individual records
5. **Student can only view**: Own attendance with statistics
6. **All changes logged**: Audit trail with before/after states

