## Frontend Integration Guide

### Step 1: Update Authentication Context

Modify [src/context/AuthContext.tsx](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20new%20updae%202.0/ldm_test/src/context/AuthContext.tsx) to use new RBAC:

```typescript
// Add role hierarchy checking
const hasPermission = (resource: string, action: string) => {
  // Call backend to verify permission
  return fetch('/php_backend/api/check_permission.php', {
    method: 'POST',
    body: JSON.stringify({ resource, action })
  });
};
```

### Step 2: Create Role-Based Routing

Update [src/App.tsx](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20new%20updae%202.0/ldm_test/src/App.tsx):

```typescript
// Protected routes based on permissions
<Route path="/admin/*" element={
  <ProtectedRoute requiredPermission="users.read">
    <AdminLayout />
  </ProtectedRoute>
} />

<Route path="/teacher/*" element={
  <ProtectedRoute requiredPermission="attendance.create">
    <TeacherLayout />
  </ProtectedRoute>
} />

<Route path="/student/*" element={
  <ProtectedRoute requireRole="student">
    <StudentLayout />
  </ProtectedRoute>
} />
```

### Step 3: Admin Panel Components

**User Management Interface:**
```typescript
// src/pages/admin/UserManagement.tsx
- DataTable with user list
- Create user modal (role selection dropdown)
- Suspend/Unsuspend action buttons
- Reset password modal
- Status badges (Active/Suspended)
```

**Attendance Management Interface:**
```typescript
// src/pages/admin/AttendanceManagement.tsx
- Filter by class, date range, teacher
- DataTable with attendance records
- Override attendance modal
- Bulk lock/unlock checkboxes
- Lock icon indicator
- Export to Excel button
```

**Audit Logs Viewer:**
```typescript
// src/pages/admin/AuditLogs.tsx
- Filterable table (user, action, date)
- Timeline view of changes
- Before/after value display
- Export functionality
```

### Step 4: Teacher Panel Components

**Attendance Marking Interface:**
```typescript
// src/pages/teacher/AttendanceMarking.tsx
- Date picker
- Class selector (only assigned classes)
